  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments used to customize a typeface when cloning it with <see cref="M:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)" />.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that holds parameters for customizing an
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface> when creating a variant via
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. It lets you select a
font collection index, choose a color palette, supply palette color overrides, and
set variation axis positions all in one call.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap or used
as a generic type argument. Use it on the stack and pass it directly to `Clone`.

## Examples

```csharp
// Clone a typeface selecting a specific named instance weight
using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("NotoSans-Variable.ttf");

var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
        {
            Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
            Value = 700,
        },
    },
};

using var bold = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
